# Type-Safe OWL Restrictions Refactoring - Complete

## Overview

Successfully refactored the ASG codebase from string-based restriction handling to type-safe OWL API
classes. Eliminated magic string comparisons throughout mapper classes, replacing
`Map<String, String>` with strongly-typed `RestrictionInfo` sealed interface.

**Status**: 🔧 In Progress - Fixing test failures

**Date Started**: February 4, 2026
**Last Updated**: February 4, 2026 (21:04 NZDT)

## Problem Statement

### Current Issue (February 4, 2026 21:00 NZDT)

**LargeApiIT tests failing** with `NullPointerException` in `DataPropertyMapper.withExample()`:

```
Caused by: java.lang.NullPointerException: Cannot invoke "String.hashCode()" because "<local2>" is null
        at com.grl.component.mapper.DataPropertyMapper.lambda$withExample$0(DataPropertyMapper.java:94)
```

**Root Cause**: The `schema.getType()` or `schema.getFormat()` was returning `null` for the
`numericValue` data property, causing the switch expression to fail when trying to hash the null
value.

**Fix Applied**: Added null checks in `withExample()` method:

- Check if `parentSchema.getType()` is null before calling `.equals()`
- Check if `schema.getType()` is null and return early if so
- Check if `schema.getFormat()` is null and provide default value
- Used nested switch with yield to handle format checking safely

**Files Modified**:

- `DataPropertyMapper.java` - Lines 91-117 (withExample method)

**Testing**: Running `mvn clean verify` to confirm fix resolves all test failures.

---

### Before Refactoring

The codebase suffered from "stringly-typed" restriction handling:

```java
// OLD: Magic string comparisons
Map<String, String> restrictions = getRestrictions();
if(restrictions.

get("someValuesFrom").

equals("")){
isRequired =false;
    }
    if(restrictions.

containsKey("minCardinality")){
int min = Integer.parseInt(restrictions.get("minCardinality"));
    schema.

setMinItems(min);
}
```

**Issues:**

- No compile-time type safety
- Runtime string parsing errors
- Scattered restriction handling logic
- Incorrect OWL semantics (someValuesFrom/allValuesFrom confusion)
- No IDE support (autocomplete, refactoring)

### After Refactoring

```java
// NEW: Type-safe pattern matching
List<RestrictionInfo> restrictions = getRestrictions();
for(
RestrictionInfo restriction :restrictions){
    switch(restriction){
    case
MinCardinality r ->schema.

setMinItems(r.expression().

getCardinality());
    case
SomeValuesFrom r ->schema.

setMinItems(1);
        case
DataOneOf oneOf ->

addEnumValues(schema, oneOf);

default ->{}
    }
    }
```

**Benefits:**

- Compile-time type checking
- Modern Java pattern matching
- Centralized OWL semantics
- IDE support and refactoring
- Self-documenting code

## Implementation Phases

### Phase 1: Create Type-Safe Restriction Data Structure ✅

**Created:** `src/main/java/com/grl/component/asg/RestrictionInfo.java`

Sealed interface with 17 record subtypes representing each OWL restriction type:

```java
public sealed interface RestrictionInfo {

  Object expression();

  default OptionalInt cardinality() {
    return OptionalInt.empty();
  }

  default Optional<? extends OWLPropertyRange> filler() {
    return Optional.empty();
  }

  // Cardinality restrictions
  record MinCardinality(OWLObjectMinCardinality expression) implements RestrictionInfo {...
  }

  record MaxCardinality(OWLObjectMaxCardinality expression) implements RestrictionInfo {...
  }

  record ExactCardinality(OWLObjectExactCardinality expression) implements RestrictionInfo {...
  }

  // Data cardinality restrictions
  record DataMinCardinality(OWLDataMinCardinality expression) implements RestrictionInfo {...
  }

  record DataMaxCardinality(OWLDataMaxCardinality expression) implements RestrictionInfo {...
  }

  record DataExactCardinality(OWLDataExactCardinality expression) implements RestrictionInfo {...
  }

  // Value restrictions
  record SomeValuesFrom(OWLObjectSomeValuesFrom expression) implements RestrictionInfo {...
  }

  record AllValuesFrom(OWLObjectAllValuesFrom expression) implements RestrictionInfo {...
  }

  record DataSomeValuesFrom(OWLDataSomeValuesFrom expression) implements RestrictionInfo {...
  }

  record DataAllValuesFrom(OWLDataAllValuesFrom expression) implements RestrictionInfo {...
  }

  // Other restrictions
  record HasValue(OWLObjectHasValue expression) implements RestrictionInfo {

  }

  record DataHasValue(OWLDataHasValue expression) implements RestrictionInfo {

  }

  record OneOf(OWLObjectOneOf expression) implements RestrictionInfo {

  }

  record DataOneOf(OWLDataOneOf expression) implements RestrictionInfo {

  }

  record UnionOf(OWLObjectUnionOf expression) implements RestrictionInfo {

  }

  record IntersectionOf(OWLObjectIntersectionOf expression) implements RestrictionInfo {

  }

  record ComplementOf(OWLObjectComplementOf expression) implements RestrictionInfo {

  }

  // Factory method with pattern matching
  static Optional<RestrictionInfo> from(OWLClassExpression expr) {
    return Optional.ofNullable(switch (expr) {
      case OWLObjectMinCardinality c -> new MinCardinality(c);
      case OWLObjectMaxCardinality c -> new MaxCardinality(c);
      case OWLObjectExactCardinality c -> new ExactCardinality(c);
      case OWLObjectSomeValuesFrom c -> new SomeValuesFrom(c);
      case OWLObjectAllValuesFrom c -> new AllValuesFrom(c);
      case OWLObjectHasValue c -> new HasValue(c);
      case OWLObjectOneOf c -> new OneOf(c);
      case OWLObjectUnionOf c -> new UnionOf(c);
      case OWLObjectIntersectionOf c -> new IntersectionOf(c);
      case OWLObjectComplementOf c -> new ComplementOf(c);
      case OWLDataMinCardinality c -> new DataMinCardinality(c);
      case OWLDataMaxCardinality c -> new DataMaxCardinality(c);
      case OWLDataExactCardinality c -> new DataExactCardinality(c);
      case OWLDataSomeValuesFrom c -> new DataSomeValuesFrom(c);
      case OWLDataAllValuesFrom c -> new DataAllValuesFrom(c);
      case OWLDataHasValue c -> new DataHasValue(c);
      case OWLDataOneOf c -> new DataOneOf(c);
      default -> null;
    });
  }

  // Apply restriction to OpenAPI ArraySchema with correct OWL semantics
  default void applyToArraySchema(io.swagger.v3.oas.models.media.ArraySchema schema) {
    switch (this) {
      case MinCardinality r -> schema.setMinItems(r.expression().getCardinality());
      case MaxCardinality r -> schema.setMaxItems(r.expression().getCardinality());
      case ExactCardinality r -> {
        schema.setMinItems(r.expression().getCardinality());
        schema.setMaxItems(r.expression().getCardinality());
      }
      case DataMinCardinality r -> schema.setMinItems(r.expression().getCardinality());
      case DataMaxCardinality r -> schema.setMaxItems(r.expression().getCardinality());
      case DataExactCardinality r -> {
        schema.setMinItems(r.expression().getCardinality());
        schema.setMaxItems(r.expression().getCardinality());
      }
      case SomeValuesFrom r -> schema.setMinItems(1); // "at least one from this set"
      case AllValuesFrom r -> {
      } // type constraint only, NO cardinality
      case DataSomeValuesFrom r -> schema.setMinItems(1);
      case DataAllValuesFrom r -> {
      } // type constraint only
      default -> {
      }
    }
  }

  // Check if restriction implies property is required (minCardinality >= 1)
  default boolean impliesRequired() {
    return switch (this) {
      case MinCardinality r -> r.expression().getCardinality() >= 1;
      case ExactCardinality r -> r.expression().getCardinality() >= 1;
      case DataMinCardinality r -> r.expression().getCardinality() >= 1;
      case DataExactCardinality r -> r.expression().getCardinality() >= 1;
      case SomeValuesFrom r -> true;
      case DataSomeValuesFrom r -> true;
      default -> false;
    };
  }

  // Check if restriction implies array (cardinality > 1 or someValuesFrom)
  default boolean impliesArray() {
    return switch (this) {
      case MinCardinality r -> r.expression().getCardinality() > 1;
      case MaxCardinality r -> r.expression().getCardinality() > 1;
      case ExactCardinality r -> r.expression().getCardinality() > 1;
      case DataMinCardinality r -> r.expression().getCardinality() > 1;
      case DataMaxCardinality r -> r.expression().getCardinality() > 1;
      case DataExactCardinality r -> r.expression().getCardinality() > 1;
      case SomeValuesFrom r -> true;
      case DataSomeValuesFrom r -> true;
      default -> false;
    };
  }
}
```

**Key Design Decisions:**

- Sealed interface ensures exhaustive pattern matching
- Record types for immutability and conciseness
- Factory method `from()` uses pattern matching for type discrimination
- Helper methods `applyToArraySchema()`, `impliesRequired()`, `impliesArray()` centralize OWL
  semantics
- Direct access to OWL expression via `expression()` method

### Phase 2: Update SchemaVisitor ✅

**Modified:** `src/main/java/com/grl/component/sdc/SchemaVisitor.java`

Added typed storage alongside existing string-based fields:

```java
// Existing fields (still used by mappers for range information)
public List<OWLObjectProperty> propertiesFromObjectRestrictions = new ArrayList<>();
