# ASG Taxonomy Processing Refactoring Plan

## Overview

Fix critical semantic errors in taxonomy handling by eliminating string-based type checking
throughout the codebase. The refactoring starts at the source (SchemaVisitor) and propagates
type-safe OWL API objects through to the mapper classes.

## Key Insight

The OWL API already provides a well-designed type hierarchy:

- `OWLObjectMinCardinality`, `OWLObjectMaxCardinality`, `OWLObjectExactCardinality` → implement
  `HasCardinality`
- `OWLObjectSomeValuesFrom`, `OWLObjectAllValuesFrom` → value restrictions
- All implement `OWLClassExpression`

**Current problem:** SchemaVisitor immediately converts these types to strings like
`["someValuesFrom", ""]`, forcing all downstream code to do string comparisons.

**Solution:** Keep OWL types through SchemaVisitor and only convert to strings at final output.

---

## Scope

**In Scope:**

- Refactor SchemaVisitor's public data members to use OWL types
- Create `RestrictionInfo` record to carry typed restriction data
- Update ResourceSchemaMapper to consume typed data
- Update all mapper classes (ObjectPropertyMapper, TaxonomyPropertyMapper, DataPropertyMapper)
- Fix incorrect `someValuesFrom`/`allValuesFrom` semantics (P0)
- Eliminate string comparisons for restriction types

---

## Phase 1: Create Typed Restriction Data Structure

**New File:** `src/main/java/com/grl/component/asg/RestrictionInfo.java`

```java
package com.grl.component.asg;

import org.semanticweb.owlapi.model.*;
import java.util.Optional;
import java.util.OptionalInt;

/**
 * Typed container for OWL restriction information.
 * Replaces the string-based Map<String, List<String>> pattern.
 */
public sealed interface RestrictionInfo {

  /** @return the original OWL class expression */
  OWLClassExpression expression();

  /** @return cardinality value if this is a cardinality restriction */
  default OptionalInt cardinality() {
    return OptionalInt.empty();
  }

  /** @return filler class/datatype if this is a value restriction */
  default Optional<? extends OWLPropertyRange> filler() {
    return Optional.empty();
  }

  // Cardinality restrictions
  record MinCardinality(OWLObjectMinCardinality expression) implements RestrictionInfo {

    @Override
    public OptionalInt cardinality() {
      return OptionalInt.of(expression.getCardinality());
    }
  }

  record MaxCardinality(OWLObjectMaxCardinality expression) implements RestrictionInfo {

    @Override
    public OptionalInt cardinality() {
      return OptionalInt.of(expression.getCardinality());
    }
  }

  record ExactCardinality(OWLObjectExactCardinality expression) implements RestrictionInfo {

    @Override
    public OptionalInt cardinality() {
      return OptionalInt.of(expression.getCardinality());
    }
  }

  // Data cardinality restrictions
  record DataMinCardinality(OWLDataMinCardinality expression) implements RestrictionInfo {

    @Override
    public OptionalInt cardinality() {
      return OptionalInt.of(expression.getCardinality());
    }
  }

  record DataMaxCardinality(OWLDataMaxCardinality expression) implements RestrictionInfo {

    @Override
    public OptionalInt cardinality() {
      return OptionalInt.of(expression.getCardinality());
    }
  }

  record DataExactCardinality(OWLDataExactCardinality expression) implements RestrictionInfo {

    @Override
    public OptionalInt cardinality() {
      return OptionalInt.of(expression.getCardinality());
    }
  }

  // Value restrictions
  record SomeValuesFrom(OWLObjectSomeValuesFrom expression) implements RestrictionInfo {

    @Override
    public Optional<OWLClassExpression> filler() {
      return Optional.of(expression.getFiller());
    }
  }

  record AllValuesFrom(OWLObjectAllValuesFrom expression) implements RestrictionInfo {

    @Override
    public Optional<OWLClassExpression> filler() {
      return Optional.of(expression.getFiller());
    }
  }

  record DataSomeValuesFrom(OWLDataSomeValuesFrom expression) implements RestrictionInfo {

    @Override
    public Optional<OWLDataRange> filler() {
      return Optional.of(expression.getFiller());
    }
  }

  record DataAllValuesFrom(OWLDataAllValuesFrom expression) implements RestrictionInfo {

    @Override
    public Optional<OWLDataRange> filler() {
      return Optional.of(expression.getFiller());
    }
  }

  // Other restrictions
  record HasValue(OWLObjectHasValue expression) implements RestrictionInfo {

  }

  record DataHasValue(OWLDataHasValue expression) implements RestrictionInfo {

  }

  record OneOf(OWLObjectOneOf expression) implements RestrictionInfo {

  }

  record DataOneOf(OWLDataOneOf expression) implements RestrictionInfo {

  }

  record UnionOf(OWLObjectUnionOf expression) implements RestrictionInfo {

  }

  record IntersectionOf(OWLObjectIntersectionOf expression) implements RestrictionInfo {

  }

  record ComplementOf(OWLObjectComplementOf expression) implements RestrictionInfo {

  }

  /**
   * Factory method to wrap an OWL class expression in the appropriate RestrictionInfo type.
   */
  static Optional<RestrictionInfo> from(OWLClassExpression expr) {
    if (expr instanceof OWLObjectMinCardinality c)
      return Optional.of(new MinCardinality(c));
    if (expr instanceof OWLObjectMaxCardinality c)
      return Optional.of(new MaxCardinality(c));
    if (expr instanceof OWLObjectExactCardinality c)
      return Optional.of(new ExactCardinality(c));
    if (expr instanceof OWLObjectSomeValuesFrom c)
      return Optional.of(new SomeValuesFrom(c));
    if (expr instanceof OWLObjectAllValuesFrom c)
      return Optional.of(new AllValuesFrom(c));
    if (expr instanceof OWLObjectHasValue c)
      return Optional.of(new HasValue(c));
    if (expr instanceof OWLObjectOneOf c)
      return Optional.of(new OneOf(c));
    if (expr instanceof OWLObjectUnionOf c)
      return Optional.of(new UnionOf(c));
    if (expr instanceof OWLObjectIntersectionOf c)
      return Optional.of(new IntersectionOf(c));
    if (expr instanceof OWLObjectComplementOf c)
      return Optional.of(new ComplementOf(c));
    if (expr instanceof OWLDataMinCardinality c)
      return Optional.of(new DataMinCardinality(c));
    if (expr instanceof OWLDataMaxCardinality c)
      return Optional.of(new DataMaxCardinality(c));
    if (expr instanceof OWLDataExactCardinality c)
      return Optional.of(new DataExactCardinality(c));
    if (expr instanceof OWLDataSomeValuesFrom c)
      return Optional.of(new DataSomeValuesFrom(c));
    if (expr instanceof OWLDataAllValuesFrom c)
      return Optional.of(new DataAllValuesFrom(c));
    if (expr instanceof OWLDataHasValue c)
      return Optional.of(new DataHasValue(c));
    if (expr instanceof OWLDataOneOf c)
      return Optional.of(new DataOneOf(c));
    return Optional.empty();
  }

  /**
   * Apply this restriction to an ArraySchema with correct OWL→OpenAPI semantics.
   */
  default void applyToArraySchema(io.swagger.v3.oas.models.media.ArraySchema schema) {
    switch (this) {
      case MinCardinality r -> schema.setMinItems(r.expression().getCardinality());
      case MaxCardinality r -> schema.setMaxItems(r.expression().getCardinality());
      case ExactCardinality r -> {
        schema.setMinItems(r.expression().getCardinality());
        schema.setMaxItems(r.expression().getCardinality());
      }
      case DataMinCardinality r -> schema.setMinItems(r.expression().getCardinality());
      case DataMaxCardinality r -> schema.setMaxItems(r.expression().getCardinality());
      case DataExactCardinality r -> {
        schema.setMinItems(r.expression().getCardinality());
        schema.setMaxItems(r.expression().getCardinality());
      }
      case SomeValuesFrom r -> {
        // someValuesFrom = "at least one from this set"
        // Set minItems=1, NO maxItems
        schema.setMinItems(1);
      }
      case AllValuesFrom r -> {
        // allValuesFrom = type constraint only, NO cardinality
        // Do nothing
      }
      case DataSomeValuesFrom r -> schema.setMinItems(1);
      case DataAllValuesFrom r -> { /* type constraint only */ }
      default -> { /* other restrictions don't affect array cardinality */ }
    }
  }

  /**
   * Check if this restriction implies the property is required (minCardinality >= 1).
   */
  default boolean impliesRequired() {
    return switch (this) {
      case MinCardinality r -> r.expression().getCardinality() >= 1;
      case ExactCardinality r -> r.expression().getCardinality() >= 1;
      case DataMinCardinality r -> r.expression().getCardinality() >= 1;
      case DataExactCardinality r -> r.expression().getCardinality() >= 1;
      case SomeValuesFrom r -> true;
      case DataSomeValuesFrom r -> true;
      default -> false;
    };
  }

  /**
   * Check if this restriction implies an array (cardinality > 1 or someValuesFrom).
   */
  default boolean impliesArray() {
    return switch (this) {
      case MinCardinality r -> r.expression().getCardinality() > 1;
      case MaxCardinality r -> r.expression().getCardinality() > 1;
      case ExactCardinality r -> r.expression().getCardinality() > 1;
      case DataMinCardinality r -> r.expression().getCardinality() > 1;
      case DataMaxCardinality r -> r.expression().getCardinality() > 1;
      case DataExactCardinality r -> r.expression().getCardinality() > 1;
      case SomeValuesFrom r -> true;
      case DataSomeValuesFrom r -> true;
      default -> false;
    };
  }
}
```

---

## Phase 2: Refactor SchemaVisitor Public Data Members

**Current (String-based):**

```java
public Map<String, List<String>> restrictionsValuesFromClass = new HashMap<>();
public Multimap<String, String> propertiesFromObjectRestrictions_ranges = HashMultimap.create();
public Multimap<String, String> propertiesFromDataRestrictions_ranges = HashMultimap.create();
```

**New (Type-safe):**

```java
// Property name → list of typed restrictions (a property can have multiple restrictions)
public Map<String, List<RestrictionInfo>> restrictions = new HashMap<>();

// Property name → filler classes (from someValuesFrom/allValuesFrom)
public Multimap<String, OWLClass> objectPropertyRanges = HashMultimap.create();
public Multimap<String, OWLDatatype> dataPropertyRanges = HashMultimap.create();

// Keep the OWL property objects (already correct)
public List<OWLObjectProperty> propertiesFromObjectRestrictions = new ArrayList<>();
public List<OWLDataProperty> propertiesFromDataRestrictions = new ArrayList<>();
```

**Update visitor methods to store typed data:**

```java

@Override
public void visit(OWLObjectSomeValuesFrom ce) {
  for (OWLObjectProperty property : ce.getObjectPropertiesInSignature()) {
    String propertyName = cleanName(sfp.getShortForm(property.getIRI()));
    if (!propertiesFromObjectRestrictions.contains(property)) {
      propertiesFromObjectRestrictions.add(property);
    }
    // Store the typed restriction
    restrictions.computeIfAbsent(propertyName, k -> new ArrayList<>())
        .add(new RestrictionInfo.SomeValuesFrom(ce));

    // Store the filler class
    if (ce.getFiller().isOWLClass() && !ce.getFiller().asOWLClass().equals(owlThing)) {
      objectPropertyRanges.put(propertyName, ce.getFiller().asOWLClass());
    }
  }
  // Handle nested expressions
  if (ce.getFiller() instanceof OWLObjectUnionOf ||
      ce.getFiller() instanceof OWLObjectIntersectionOf ||
      ce.getFiller() instanceof OWLObjectOneOf) {
    ce.getFiller().accept(this);
  }
}

@Override
public void visit(OWLObjectMinCardinality ce) {
  for (OWLObjectProperty property : ce.getObjectPropertiesInSignature()) {
    String propertyName = cleanName(sfp.getShortForm(property.getIRI()));
    if (!propertiesFromObjectRestrictions.contains(property)) {
      propertiesFromObjectRestrictions.add(property);
    }
    restrictions.computeIfAbsent(propertyName, k -> new ArrayList<>())
        .add(new RestrictionInfo.MinCardinality(ce));

    if (ce.getFiller().isOWLClass()) {
      objectPropertyRanges.put(propertyName, ce.getFiller().asOWLClass());
    }
  }
}
// ... similar for other visitor methods
```

---

## Phase 3: Update ResourceSchemaMapper

**Current (convoluted string transformation, lines 130-140):**

```java
